[{"id":"VR876707","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Monochromatic light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub X\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> passes through two closely-spaced, parallel slits, producing an interference pattern on a screen some distance away from the slits. The distance from the central maximum to the center of the first-order maximum is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub 1 comma X, end sub\"><math alttext=\"s sub 1 comma X, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>s</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. Next, monochromatic light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub Y equals three halves lambda sub X\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub Y equals three halves lambda sub X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mi>Y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>λ</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> passes through the same slits and produces an interference pattern on the same screen. In the new pattern, the distance from the central maximum to the center of the <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">second</span>-order maximum is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub 2 comma Y, end sub\"><math alttext=\"s sub 2 comma Y, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>s</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. What is the ratio <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub 2 comma Y, end sub, to s sub 1 comma X, end sub\"><math alttext=\"s sub 2 comma Y, end sub, to s sub 1 comma X, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>s</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>s</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>? Assume that the light forming both interference patterns is directed at small angles from the incident light direction.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876707_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\" the ratio 3 to 1\"><math alttext=\" the ratio 3 to 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\" the ratio 3 to 2\"><math alttext=\" the ratio 3 to 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\" the ratio 3 to 4\"><math alttext=\" the ratio 3 to 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\" the ratio 4 to 3\"><math alttext=\" the ratio 4 to 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]